text: The 2020 United States presidential election in North Dakota was held on Tuesday, November 3, 2020, as part of the 2020 United States presidential election. Incumbent President Donald Trump and his running mate Vice President Mike Pence had won 3 electoral votes in the Electoral College. == References == Category:2020 United States presidential election Category:History of North Dakota
title: 2020 United States presidential election in North Dakota
